result.name: Cafe Hunan 書湘門第

reviews.text: Service and environment is satisfactory but the food is, at best, just average. After reading the attractive menu, we ordered 3 dishes: pig-ear, pork belly (毛氏紅燒肉) and stirred fried noodles, a bottle of beer and a bowl of white rice with some expectation but we are let down. The cartilage of the pig-ear is “hard”, pork-belly is dry and not tender (of course I mean the lean parts, to me it’s like frozen meat), and the fried noodle is alright but a bit oily. Also note that even we have asked to have the lowest level of spiciness （微辣）, the dishes are still very spicy for us. Not likely to be going again.
Authentic Hunan style restaurant, reasonable price.
Absolutely fantastic restaurant. Every dishes I have tried are stunning. Be careful when ordering the fish, the size of the dish is huge
Excellent spicy food offered. Comfortable seating.
Better to go for lunch coz the lunch set is much cheaper than dinner

result.name: 書湘門第

reviews.text:
東西好吃 服務也不錯
但是整間餐廳 吵到不行 有時候會聽不見同行友人說話
餐廳生意很好、9成都是大陸客、我完全明白吃飯聊天很正常 、但是音量真的太大了。難道都沒考慮的隔壁桌的還有人在用餐嗎？ 那桌客人跟廚房熟識、兩邊竟然隔空對話、廚師還手裡握著煙出來含喧。拜託 ！我是來吃飯的不是來聽噪音跟吸二手菸的 好嗎！

The cartilage of the pig-ear is “hard”, pork-belly is dry and not tender (of course I mean the lean parts, to me it’s like frozen meat), and the fried noodle is alright but a bit oily. Also note that even we have asked to have the lowest level of spiciness （微辣）, the dishes are still very spicy for us. Not likely to be going again.
地方比較窄，不過好多內地人來到光顧。食物頗為惹味
好味，但水準不穩定
價格優惠，口味正宗，適合聚會一起吃，自己一人買個炒飯外帶也很方便
